1. Calculate the following numerical results to three decimal places using R. [Note: Function “ln” means the natural log function]

  1. \((7 - 8) + 5^3 - 5 / 6 + \sqrt{62}\)
  2. \(\ln 3 + \sqrt 2 \sin(\pi) - e^3\)
  3. \(\ln 5 - exp(2) + 2^3\)
# a
a <- (7 - 8) + (5 ^ 3) - (5 / 6) + (sqrt(62))

# b
b <- log(3) + (sqrt(2)) * sin(pi) - exp(1)^3

# c
c <- log(5) - exp(2) + 2^3

sprintf("a: %.3f", round(a, digits = 3))
## [1] "a: 131.041"
sprintf("b: %.3f", round(b, digits = 3))
## [1] "b: -18.987"
sprintf("c: %.3f", round(c, digits = 3))
## [1] "c: 2.220"
  1. Create a vector named countby5 that is a sequence of 5 to 100 in steps of 5.
countby5 <- seq(5, 100, by = 5)

## [20] 100
  1. Provide the missing values in rep(seq(, , ), ) to create the sequence 20, 15, 15, 10, 10, 10, 5, 5, 5, 5.
rep_seq <- rep(seq(20, 5, by = -5), 1:4)
print(rep_seq)
##  [1] 20 15 15 10 10 10  5  5  5  5
  1. Solve the following system of equations using R. \[ 3x + 2y + 1z = 10 \\ 2x - 3y + 1z = -1 \\ 1x + 1y + 1z = 6 \]
m_a <- rbind(c(3, 2, 1), c(2, -3, 1), c(1, 1, 1))
m_b <- c(10, -1, 6)
solved <- solve(m_a, m_b)
x <- solved[1]
y <- solved[2]
z <- solved[3]
sprintf("x = %.0f :: y = %.0f :: z = %.0f", x, y, z)
## [1] "x = 1 :: y = 2 :: z = 3"
